OL,6,FIf those involved fail to comply with
OL,7,Fthese notices, a report will be
OL,8,Fsubmitted to the procurator fiscal
OL,9,F(public prosecutor in Scotland) for
OL,10,Fconsideration of a prosecution, where
OL,11,Fthe offender could face imprisonment,
OL,12,Fa significant fine, or both.
OL,14,FCouncillor Ruairi Kelly, Glasgow's
OL,15,Fconvener for neighbourhood services,
OL,16,Fsaid: "Action has been taken by the
OL,17,Fcouncil's Environmental Health team in
OL,18,Fa bid to prevent procedures being
OL,19,Fcarried out in unsuitable and non-
OL,20,Fsterile locations.
